trans-unit.source: A collection of <xref href="System.Xml.Schema.XmlSchemaObject"></xref>s.
Initializes a new instance of the `XmlSchemaObjectCollection` class.
Initializes a new instance of the `XmlSchemaObjectCollection` class that takes an <xref href="System.Xml.Schema.XmlSchemaObject"></xref>.
The <xref href="System.Xml.Schema.XmlSchemaObject"></xref>.
Adds an <xref href="System.Xml.Schema.XmlSchemaObject"></xref> to the `XmlSchemaObjectCollection`.

If `Count` already equals the capacity, the capacity of list is doubled by automatically reallocating the internal array and copying the existing elements to the new array before the new element is added.
If `Count` is less than the capacity, this method is an 0(1) operation.
If the capacity needs to be increased to accommodate the new element, this method becomes an 0(n) operation, where n is `Count`.

The <xref:System.Xml.Schema.XmlSchemaObjectCollection.Add%2A> method expects only <xref:System.Xml.Schema.XmlSchemaExternal> and its derived types (<xref:System.Xml.Schema.XmlSchemaImport>, <xref:System.Xml.Schema.XmlSchemaInclude>, and <xref:System.Xml.Schema.XmlSchemaRedefine>) as parameters.
The following example illustrates adding an included schema to the <xref:System.Xml.Schema.XmlSchema.Includes%2A> collection of an existing <xref:System.Xml.Schema.XmlSchema> object.

Removes an <xref href="System.Xml.Schema.XmlSchemaObject"></xref> from the `XmlSchemaObjectCollection`.
This method performs a linear search; therefore, the average execution time is proportional to <xref:System.Collections.CollectionBase.Count%2A>.
That is, this method is an O(`n`) operation, where `n` is <xref:System.Collections.CollectionBase.Count%2A>.
This method determines equality by calling <xref:System.Object.Equals%2A>.
The elements that follow the removed element move up to occupy the vacated spot.
